RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 52000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $100,000 (Purse $65,000 For Horses That Qualify For Maiden Dirt Bonus).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACE OF CLUBS broke out and bumped BOWTIE BOYS, chased off the inside early, took aim two wide into the lane, drew alongside the runner-up in deep stretch and drove past. ELIGIO dueled for the lead from inside, inched clear around the turn, showed the way into the final sixteenth and could not fend off the winner. ALWAYS ON CAY shifted in early and corrected before going between foes to challenge for the lead, dueled outside ELIGIO into and around the turn, lost touch with that rival three wide leaving the bend, weakened in the final furlong and saved the show. THOMPSON raced up close outside the top pair early, chased three then four wide around the turn and flattened in the lane. BOWTIE BOYS took a bump from inside at the start, coaxed along early in mid-pack, went three wide into the turn, exited five wide and lacked the needed response. RINGTONE sat off the pace from inside, tipped out and came three wide into the lane and failed to menace. READY TO STORM chased three wide into the turn, four wide into the drive and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 32000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. T'S THIRSTY pressed from inside early then took a stalking position on the backstretch, tipped two wide around the far turn, bid inside past the quarter pole, took over in upper stretch and held well through the final sixteenth. MAC'S TIME vied three deep into the clubhouse turn then pressed from outside, took over early on the far turn, vied two wide into the lane, lost command in upper stretch but stayed on well to the wire. CHICKNFINGERFRIDAY brushed with outer rival prior to the first turn, chased in the two path around both bends, tipped out and made contact with rival in upper stretch, drifted in and bumped rival past the sixteenth pole and was along for the show. STOTLAND chased five deep into the first turn then dropped back and angled down to the two path, moved out on the backstretch to take closer order, bid three wide around the far turn, could not keep up with the top pair into the lane, flattened in the furlong grounds and took a bump from CHICKNFINGERFRIDAY late. CURLY ESA got bumped between rivals early, tracked three deep around the first turn, moved out and came five wide into the stretch and could not rally. BIG SWEDE got bumped from inside before the first turn, chased four deep early, three then four wide on the far turn, got brushed from by inner rival at the top of the lane and weakened. DIVINE FEMININE settled along the inside, angled out on the far turn and came five wide into the drive and failed to menace. MUHAMMAD ALI (PER) vied between rivals then took control on the clubhouse turn, set a pressured pace up the backstretch, lost command early on the far turn, started to weaken around the bend and faded through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. T's Thirsty
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, stalked, tipped 2wide, bid inside 1/4, best late

ENTRY.OWNER: Rancho San Roberto Inc and Spasiano Alexander J
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, set pressured pace, overtaken 2nd, gave way

ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed early, chased 2wide, bumped upper & 1/16, gain 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Big Swede
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped early, chased 4deep, 3-4wide, brushed upper, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Stotland
ENTRY.OWNER: Featherston Roger Lambert Jeffrey Stotland Peter and Underhill Peter G

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 82000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOUBLE JAB rated in a stalking position on the inside early, tipped two wide around the bend, reached the front with a furlong remaining, kicked clear shortly after and won going away. GRAND TIGER set the pace under pressure early, cleared along the inside around the bend, relinquished the lead at the eighth pole and stayed on to hold the place. GRAZED stalked outside a rival into the turn, was caught behind LORD TRIPPING around the bend and altered to the inside, kept on through the lane but could only earn the show honors. GIANOLA chased along the inside out of range, cut the corner into the stretch and improved position. LORD TRIPPING prompted the pace from outside early, failed to stay with the leader around the bend, chased three wide into the drive and flattened out. BLACK AS MY HEART traveled four deep near the back into and around the bend and failed to threaten. TOPPERS WAGER chased between rivals in the two path off the pace and proved no menace. GHOSTLY ACT raced three deep into and around the turn and could not respond when called upon. NAHAN trailed on the inside to the stretch and made no impact.

ENTRY.NAME: Double Jab
ENTRY.OWNER: Eaton James A and Muldoon Don

ENTRY.NAME: Nahan
ENTRY.OWNER: Branch William A Pagano Michael Sackett Rick Sackett Mrs Rick and Wallace II Jer

ENTRY.NAME: Grazed
ENTRY.OWNER: Shanderella Stables and Anderson Robert W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 101. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 83000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming, Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $16,000 Or Less In The Last 2 Starts Preferred)(HORSES THAT ARE ENTERED FOR CLAIMING PRICE ARE RUNNING FOR A PURSE OF $46,000).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEMON SUSHI stalked up the backstretch, bid outside the leader at the seven-sixteenths pole, took over around the turn, moved over to the inside while dueling with SAULS CALL past the quarter pole, cleared into the stretch, showed the way into the final sixteenth and lasted over the late bid from the runner-up. SUPER CHIEF raced up close on the inside, tipped two wide on the turn, launched a late bid in deep stretch and missed. WINDRIBBON tracked from inside early, found traffic briefly behind GOLDENSUNRISE at the quarter pole, altered out to the two path and finished willingly down the lane for a clear third. BIG HAND chased widest up the backstretch, navigated the turn four to five wide and could not rally in the furlong grounds. SEATTLE BREAKOUT climbed early and dropped back, trailed into the turn, came six wide into the lane and summoned a mild rally. SAULS CALL chased four wide into the turn, launched a bid from outside around the bend but could not stay with the winner late on the turn, entered the stretch three wide and weakened. HANDSOME GARY dropped back early, raced along the rail on the turn, tipped three wide outside a pair of rivals entering the stretch and could not rally. GOLF DRAMA forwardly placed three deep into the turn, remained three wide to the stretch and flattened. MYSTIC FLYER chased three deep into the turn, got bumped by inner rival at the five-sixteenths pole, eased out and came five wide into the stretch and could not rally. WHAT AN IDEA raced in range early then started to climb and lost ground, drifted out into rival and steadied near the five-sixteenths pole, lost positions around the bend after and had little left for the drive. GOLDENSUNRISE stumbled at the start then recovered and went up to take control early, was challenged from outside at the seven-sixteenths pole, lost command with three furlongs remaining and retreated.

ENTRY.COMMENT: up close inside, tipped 2wide, late bid, missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 5 5F Turf CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 82000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRANCINGTHRUPARIS away quickly from outside to take control but was soon confronted by O MANDY from inside, lost command leaving the backstretch but fought back through the turn, regained control entering the stretch, cleared inner rival with a furlong remaining and held late. RUNAMILEINMYSHOES got forced in leaving the gate and lost ground, moved into range along the inside up the backstretch, traveled on the inside to two wide around the bend, moved out in the lane and put in a late bid but could not get by. O MANDY was off a bit slow and inward to begin then went up to duel with the winner from inside, took over nearing the turn, battled around the bend but relinquished the lead turning for home, lost touch with the winner at the eighth pole but stayed on to the wire. ASADA FRIES was off slow to begin, sat off the pace then angled to the inside for the turn, saved ground to the stretch, then came with a belated rally to pick up a minor share. SMOOVE OVER became fractious in the gate, hustled from the gate then had to pause when the leader crossed over into her path, chased from out of range two wide into the turn, angled to the inside around the bend, steered out in the drive and kept on while unable to threaten. LONGHORN LASSIE raced up close early then drifted out near the half-mile pole, drifted out again on the turn and weakened. RUBY'S HOME broke a step slow and was green early while losing her path, trailed into and around the turn and failed to menace.

ENTRY.OWNER: Red Baron's Barn LLC and Rancho Temescal LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in start, inside-2wide, late bid

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, green, lost path early, no menace

ENTRY.COMMENT: up close early, drifted out 1/2 & turn, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Graduation S. DEL MAR RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 95. Stakes Purse 125000. FOR GOLDEN STATE SERIES ELIGIBLE CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED TWO-YEAR-OLDS. By subscription of $125 each, which shall accompany the nomination, Closed Thursday August 3,2023 with 10 or by supplementary nomination of $1,250 each. (non-Golden Stat e Series eligible horses, $25,000 to supplement -- which will make that horse eligible to all future Golden State Series Stakes) by closing time of entries. All horses to pay $1,875 additional to start, with $125,000 Guaranteed, of which $71,250 to first, $23,750 to second, $15,000 to third, $7,500 to fourth, $5,000 to fifth and $2,500 to sixth. Weight 122 lbs.; Non-winners of two races other than claiming allowed 2 lbs.; of a race other than claiming, 4 lbs. High weights preferred. Total earnings in non- claiming races will be used in determining the preference of horses with equal weights. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORD PRANCEALOT sped clear and crossed over, felt some pressure from outside on the turn before clearing again past the quarter pole, put to right handed urging and held over the late bid from LAST CALL LONDON in the closing moments. LAST CALL LONDON broke a step slow and lost hist path at the start, climbed a bit then settled into stride and started to gain along the fence up the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, moved off the fence in the drive, challenged the winner from outside late but ran out of time. MICI'S EXPRESS dropped back early, went two wide into the turn, advanced while easing further out and came four wide into the stretch, closed well in the final furlong and gained the show. REFOCUS stalked the leader inside a rival to the turn, put in a mild bid from outside around the bend but failed to keep up with LORD PRANCEALOT past the quarter pole, continued within range entering the final furlong but could not summon the needed late kick in deep stretch. WILD JEWELS chased widest up the backstretch, went seven wide into the turn, moved into the four path around the bend and could not rally. SHADY APPEAL stalked the pacesetter outside a rival, traveled three deep around the turn, took an awkward step entering the stretch and faded out of contention. SMOKEM EZ came away slow, chased five wide into the turn, lost ground around the bend and came three wide into the stretch and weakened. SALSATION tracked six wide into the turn, was forced to check near the five-sixteenths pole, moved in and exited the three wide and had little left for the stretch run.

ENTRY.OWNER: London Tom Lovingier Terry C and Zondlo Eugene
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow/lost path, climbed bit, gained inside, late bid, missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 92. Claiming Purse 35000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000. (Rail at 24 feet).

CLAIM.OWNER: Fritts Marie J Graves Stephanie Pellman Harry and Seymour Lauri

RACE.FOOTNOTES: INNER BEAUTY (IRE) dueled for the lead from inside then took control around the clubhouse turn, cleared at the five-eighths pole, showed the way to the top of the stretch, continued clear into deep stretch and was able to hold on over late charging rivals. ABHITA broke a step slow, settled inside, looked to start a rally leaving the far turn but got put in a bit tight, gained a clear path and moved out in the lane, tried to split foes and bumped with outer rival at the sixteenth pole, surged late and missed. DOLLY MAY (IRE) tracked on the inside, two wide on the far turn, closed through the lane and got bumped by ABHITA at the sixteenth pole and finished gamely to the wire. DOWNBURST stalked the pace from inside, roused late on the far turn, tipped out in the stretch to take aim at the winner, altered in late and got outfinished. CORPORAL VIOLETTE (IRE) broke a bit slow, pulled hard early between rivals, got boxed in on the far turn, spun four wide into the lane and lacked a rally. SHEZMISBEHAVING broke a step slow, trailed on the inside into the first turn, continued at the rear three wide into the lane and passed tired rivals. GOLDEN TEMPER stalked in the two path, three deep with a quarter mile left to run and lacked a response when called upon. ASPIRATIONAL settled three deep early, traveled four deep on the far turn, five wide into the stretch and came up empty. ILA VEIW TOO dueled for the lead from outside into the first turn, ceded command around the bend then took a stalking position in the middle stages, coaxed around the far turn in the two path and faded down the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Claiming Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALL THE KING'S MEN bumped leaving the gate, stalked four deep early, bid four then three wide on the far turn, took over in upper stretch, dueled with BIG GUN in the final furlong and gamely prevailed. BIG GUN closest in pursuit from the two path, lost positions and came under ride on the far turn, cut the corner into the stretch, challenged inside rivals at the eighth pole, battled with ALL THE KING'S MEN to the wire and could not get by. LEN'S LUCK raced two wide near the back early on, rounded the far turn three wide, summoned a mild rally and was along for the show. MONTANA chased three deep early, between foes into the far turn, spun three wide into the lane and could not find the needed late kick in the final furlong and got edged for the show. BUFFETT stepped to the front from inside, led two to three wide into the lane, lost command in upper stretch and weakened. COMMISSIONER H bobbled leaving the gate, settled inside and failed to rally. RIPPIN' RUIS (AUS) bumped with outer rival then steadied shortly after, got bumped between rivals five wide into the first turn, chased two wide off the pace into the stretch and lacked a rally. ICE STORM drifted out to bother rivals entering the first turn, remained off the inside up the backstretch, rounded the far turn three then four wide and came up empty. L L L COOL rated in the two path early, chased in range up the backstretch, dropped back under asking on the far turn and tired. AMERICAN EMPIRE was off a bit slow from outside, got bumped entering the first turn six wide, remained wide to the far turn, came five wide into the stretch and proved no menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2wide, inside, bid upper, dueled str, denied
